 won't stack with item haste.<br>It's a really bad idea if you ask me to not use a haste item over something that gives ac. You are losing out in a very significant amount of damage for extremely negligable gains in ac. <br>Throw away those ac items and get hasted!!! You'll never turn back.<br>Haste &gt; ac/resists/hp/wis in pretty much all situations.<br>Sure if you are backup cleric and aren't doing any melee than it might not be as useful if you want to max your wis or something, but you should still own one and use it the other 90% of the time. At L50+ with the gear in some of those profiles, there's no reason why they can't afford an FBSS or similar haste item. <br><br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilfalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gilfalas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1474<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/25/02 11:56:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> All I know is this, I regular XP now with two monks, first is a level 60 Iksar with Epic, Cowl of Mortality and a Sceptre of Mastery; second is a 59 Human with Epic, Rune Branded Girdle, Sceptre of Mastery and Stave of Shielding. Since monk haste stacks with all (least that is what they tell me) they are pretty bada$$ damage machines.<br><br>But when we XP I always tank. I use ONE Cease on the mob as it is pulled in and with Shroud of the Dar Brood, Valor of Marr and Nature's Defender I EASILY maintain aggro. I MAY have to hit Taunt once a fight while both these monks pound on it's back.<br><br>Haste totally rules and never let anyone tell you otherwise.<br><br>And strangley enough on a tangental note, I have tried using various one handers to keep aggro whiel MTing and I find in ALL cases that my Nature's Defender generates far more aggro than either my Sword of Blessings or my Massive Dragonclaw Shard. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105286">Gilfalas Elaandrin</a>, Lvl 59 Knight of Tunare & Defender of Nature<br>Bertoxxulous Server<br><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">Paladins Of Norrath</a> Messageboard Admin<br>Member of <a href="http://www.fedupnow.com/">Dragon Council</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 206<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 3:43:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> Those of us who do not have haste, probably can't afford it. I know I would have Haste if I had ever had 4k at once (FBSS). (trades I could offer are worth almost nothing, except to the destroy button.) I'm not 50+, but very close to it now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urendaelbrigh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rendael Brigh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 5:15:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> With two camps of the shrunken goblin skull earring I made 14k. There are various ways to get money if you have the time, patience, etc. <p>Rendael Brigh<BR>Knight of Truth, 55th shield<BR>Avengers Federation<BR>Tholuxe Paells<BR>Master Smith 208<BR>Master Brewer 146<BR>Master Potter 124<BR>Journeyman Tailor 65<BR>Master Baker 102<BR><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=122156" target="_new">My Magelo character profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukilmarfyrewynd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilmar Fyrewynd</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 674<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 8:30:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> Killing Hill Giants in Rathe Mountains for a week could easily yield a FBSS. Hell, if you're near the mid 50s and you still don't have a haste sash, something is DEFINITELY wrong. <p><b><i><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=74373>Kilmar Fyrewynd</a><BR>60th Crusader<BR><a href=http://www.farrout.net/kingscourt/>King's Court</a><BR>Drinal Server<BR></b></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilfalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gilfalas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1483<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 9:01:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> Haste is hard to come by pre 45 but FBSS's are now so common that 4K can get you one. Amd for anyoen in level 35-50, 4K is NOT that difficult to aquire, even if you are a casual player. Just make sure you carry a lot of empty bags, max out what you can carry in FS and/or hunt Firiona Vie Giants. They drop crap weapons that sell for 45-70 plat each, and tunic and hats in similar price ranges.<br><br>4K is defiantely do-able for even casual players who put forth the effort and have a little luck.<br><br>For the unlucky, well nothing you can do about that. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105286">Gilfalas Elaandrin</a>, Lvl 59 Knight of Tunare & Defender of Nature<br>Bertoxxulous Server<br><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">Paladins Of Norrath</a> Messageboard Admin<br>Member of <a href="http://www.fedupnow.com/">Dragon Council</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dyermaker>Dyermaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 9:42:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> I managed to get an FBSS for 1000PP and an FRSS this weekend. FRSS was only selling for about 500PP. Haste is available if you're looking. <p>Dyermaker Merdinho -- The Lost Paladin and Lil'Bastard<BR>42 Paladin of Tunare, Quellious Server<BR>Profiles: <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32626">Magelo<A> -- <A HREF="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/userinfo.html?char=16712">Allakhazam</A> --<A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=3366">Caster's Realm</A><BR>Lil'Bastard Clan: <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32626">Dyermaker</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91012">Chapado</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115022">Chiad</A>  | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82578">Malvado</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=92554">Narnya</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=111438">Solyony</A> <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 863<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 11:30:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> Yeah and some of the profiles have very nice items. easily some 5-10kpp+ items so it's not an issue of plat. It's an issue of being uninformed or incorrectly thinking it's better to wear a 10ac belt than a 21% haste belt.<br>10-15ac is going to save you maybe 2-3% damage taken.<br>21% haste is going to increase your damage output by 17%.<br>(I think that's how it works. 21% haste = 21% delay reduction or a 17% increase in attacks. regardless it's going to increase your damage by min 17%)<br><br>So the mob can either kill you 3% slower or you can kill the mob 17% faster. Which would you choose? It's pretty obvious to me.<br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 318<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 12:05:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> If you do not mind destroying coldain faction, coldain heads are a very good income source. 100pp per head from players if common and you get about 4 per hour. <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalantia>Dalantia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 3:16:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> I'm not 50+, but I can think of a few reasons:<br><br>98% of their gear is hand-me-downs or guild equipment that they can't or would feel bad selling.<br><br>All of their gear has been picked up through drops and they have a very limited cashflow, and are more interested in experience than just farming cash.  I know this applies to me: as far as I'm concerned, a night spent just killing things for cash is a wasted night, and I consider myself obscenely lucky if I have more than 100 plat in the bank at any given time.<br><br>Um.. that's about it.  Thought I had more, but don't. *grins*<br><br>Dal Dragonet<br>Aiyeka's Beloved Guardian, 42nd Rank<br>Fennin Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 835<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 4:04:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/skfitz/valface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> It's a good bet that the 50+ without haste simply don't fully grasp the difference it makes, or overestimate the damage add they get from STR (many of the common belt options like TBB and the Belt of Defense from ME have the virtue of a nice STR bonus) or AC.  They may also be reluctant to spend the money although these days, FBSS goes for 2k on my server....<br><br>They MAY think Valor of Marr doesn't stack with items, or conversely, they may think VoM stacks with chanter, shaman, and bard haste, making item haste "unnecessary" (it doesn't stack with those, it's spell haste just as those 3 are).<br><br>Even if you don't have the cash, get to Frenzy and get a FBSS, or at least do the Stonebrunt quest I heard of to get a 15% item. I wore the FBSS I won at 51 until I received a hand-me-down Sash of the Dragonborne from a guildmate at about 57, which I finally replaced at 59 with a Girdle of Faith. What a nice difference the 41% haste made over the approx. 20% haste of the first 2 items; well, getting a FBSS would make just as nice a difference from no haste at all.<br><br> <p>Valya Wanderfoot, 60 paladin<br><hr width="240">"I really didn'trealize the librarians were, you know, such adangerous group.... subversive. You think they're just sitting there at the desk, all quiet andeverything. They're like plotting the revolution, man. I wouldn't mess with them." --Michael Moore, 2002</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useanen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seanen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 5:07:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> One comment, IMO of course.<br><br>If you're using an Axegoreth's belt for the STR bonus, you're doing something wrong.  15 wis is where it's at.<br><br>If you're one of those who primarily do things with your guild, and you have primarily guild items, take a look at my <a href = http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2116> profile </a>.  The haste cloak was a hand me down from a guild ranger who had that and an RBG.  I was able to take my dragonborn sash off and put my Axegoreth's belt on this way.<br><br>All of the stuff in my profile (I think) was given to me by my guild(s) (I was an officer before the guild I was in merged with my current).  So it is possible, even without having a ton of money.<br><br>Now, leading raids for months is a pain, but other than that...  =b <p><center><img src = http://home.att.net/~rpmorri/Seanensig.jpg></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 837<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 5:34:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/skfitz/valface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> I'm not saying the STR would be the only reason to use that belt, just that some folks might mistakenly think it offsets the increased damage of a haste belt.   & part of my post was to point out that you can get haste items w/o money too, I've never paid for one but rather won them / received from guild / quested with help of guild. <p>Valya Wanderfoot, 60 paladin<br><hr width="240">"I really didn'trealize the librarians were, you know, such adangerous group.... subversive. You think they're just sitting there at the desk, all quiet andeverything. They're like plotting the revolution, man. I wouldn't mess with them." --Michael Moore, 2002</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukeamilkindhearted00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KeamilKindhearted00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 5:45:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> Well regardless of cash, etc...How often do you 50+ actually group without an enchanter...Very rarely...Not only, by then do you have an AUTO 25percent haste, but id say screw the fbss...Sell it for 5k cash, pick up Thunder etched gaunts/Tbb...You most ALWAYS have an enchanter with you..since dly cant go below 11, there is actually no point to have any...unless its a COF, RBB, RBG...Etc, there is very little need...<br>Personally at 50, id rather get That guard of haste/Chromatic boots for the 6percent...than have a 50 percent haste + enchanter <p>Keamil Kindhearted<Br> 46th Knight <Br>Steel Thunder <Br> <a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=145322">Muh Sutff</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujaelprayerblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jael Prayerblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 5:54:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> I for one do not use a haste item, only for the fact that the amount of haste the fbss I had did not stack up to the 20 ac and 15 str and 15 wis I lost from the belt of defense.<br><br>Also Pally's are a defensive tank, so Im not gonna lose the 20 ac for a little bit of haste.  Im soloing in Guk now quite easily, can take 2 dars at a time and not lose half my hp.  <br><br>When I raid or group, there is usually a chanter around for haste and I get it that way.  Heres my stuff anyway.<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=145351">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=145351</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p><center><img src="http://www.illumincathari.com/images/profile/jael_sig.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 838<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 7:00:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/skfitz/valface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> The last 2 posters exemplify my point.  I happen to respectfully disagree with both but that is the reasoning some use.<br><br>my view:  20% haste > any non-haste item for belt slot. If you solo, the fight will be 20% shorter.  The added 15AC from your belt does not mitigate damge 20%.  If you choose to value the 15 strength and wisdom that highly, that is subjective & your choice; it is not mine. <br><br>Chanter haste stacks with haste items. The fastest chanter haste is 70% leaving plenty of room for improvement with a haste item. Chanter/bard/shaman haste will NOT stack with Valor of Marr so for grouping, Valor of Marr is irrelevant.  For soloing, Valor of Marr + a haste item is vastly superior to Valor of Marr w/o a haste item. <p>Valya Wanderfoot, 60 paladin<br><hr width="240">"I really didn'trealize the librarians were, you know, such adangerous group.... subversive. You think they're just sitting there at the desk, all quiet andeverything. They're like plotting the revolution, man. I wouldn't mess with them." --Michael Moore, 2002</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujaelprayerblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jael Prayerblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 8:06:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> I am saying that I will not use a haste item, unless it offsets some of the ac/str/wis or other stats that I will be losing.  Its a complete joke to use a fbss instead of an Axegoraths belt of Defense.  You are a defensive tank, not a warrior or a monk, leave the damage to them.  I cannot at this time justify 21% haste and losing 30 total AC with 15 str and 15 wis.  So what if I have to fight for 12 seconds longer out of a minute fight, thats one less Hat heal Ill have to do, if I use a 0 ac item in the belt slot.<br><br>However thats not to say I will never use a haste item, But it better be a worth while trade of stats/AC.   <p><center><img src="http://www.illumincathari.com/images/profile/jael_sig.jpg"></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujaelprayerblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jael Prayerblade</A> at: 3/26/02 8:09:17 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushehabaldean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shehab al dean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arabian Crusader</span><br>  Posts: 544<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 4:05:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://forzaq8.net/everquest/personal.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> without haste will be wasting more heals and time on a mob<br>and doing more heals = more down time to reg mana<br><br>the less you med and use helm heal the more you are killing<br>you will be getting more kills per hour <br><br>if you are care so much that you don't lose AC / stat  get a POA haste belt , any haste is better than no haste<br><br>when you fight a mob , you don't want to kill it solwly , you want to kill it fast , your haste will mean less med time for you if your solo'ing , or your guild if you are killing a mob , aka more kills , less time doing raid<br><br>balance <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11584">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...?num=11584</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 320<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 6:09:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> I do not like to believe in assumptions or common knowledge. So went a ran some numbers comparing AC20 belt with FBSS.<br><br>Each time you add 50AC your damage taken will go down around 15%. So the 20 raw/30 effective AC from the ME belt would reduce your damage taken by 9%.<br><br>Let's make up a fight. Mob takes 5 min to kill, deals 5 HP damage per second. This numbers are without wearing a belt yet. Now lets compare the fights with first the ME belt, then wearing a FBSS.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    ME belt (AC20 STR/WIS15) </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Damage taken is reduced by 9% due to better AC down to 4.55 dmg/sec<br><br>Total damage taken is 300 seconds * 4.55 dmg/sec.<br><br>Total damage = 1365 HP<br>Fight time = 300 seconds<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    FBSS </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Damage taken is still 5 dmg/sec. Fight time is reduced by 21% down to 237 second versus the 300 seconds for 5 min.<br><br>Total damage = 1185 HP<br>Fight time = 237 seconds<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Solo Conclussion </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Make your choice, would you like to fight something for 5 min and take 1365HPs damage or would you rather fight approximately 4 min and only take 1185HPs. Clear choice here that FBSS rules over ME belt.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Group Choice </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Refined the test example some. I choose a 6000 HP mob that deals 5HP/sec damage again. Each group member deals 20 DPS. Case A is wearing ME belt, case B is with FBSS. You are taking all hits as a main tank. ME belt reduces damage by 9% and FBSS increases your DPS to 24.2.<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>paladin + 1 other meele</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>ME belt: 171 second fight/780 damage taken<br>FBSS: 136 second fight/679 damage taken<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>paladin + 2 other meele</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>ME belt: 109 second fight/496 damage taken<br>FBSS: 93 second fight/467 damage taken<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>paladin + 3 other meele</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>ME belt: 80 second fight/364 damage taken<br>FBSS: 71 second fight/356 damage taken<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>paladin + 4 other meele</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>ME belt: 62 second fight/284 damage taken<br>FBSS: 58 second fight/288 damage taken<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>paladin + 5 other meele</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>ME belt:  52 second fight/235 damage taken<br>FBSS: 48 second fight/242 damage taken<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Group Conclusion </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Except for a group with 5 or 6 meele dealing damage, the FBSS always kills faster with less damage taken. In the 5 and 6 meele groups the FBSS group will still kill 5% faster with maybe 1% more damage taken.<br><br>The assumption that adding 30 effective AC will make a better tank out of you over no AC and haste is not correct.<br><br>FBSS &gt;&gt; AC20 belt in all possible circumstances. <br><br>I played around and a AC40 belt(raw AC) would compensate for no wearing a FBSS.<br><br>Modifying the HP of the mob, damage output of the mob will not change the difference between ME belt and FBSS. <br><br>The ME belt only becomes an option over the FBSS when you main tank raids with 12+ people. Then the damage output of the MT becomes less relevant.<br><br>(Got these numbers for damage reduction by increasing AC from parses taken with 1000AC-1350AC in increments of 50AC. Not sure how applicable that is when you have below 1000AC. Obviously also depends on what the mobs attack rating is)<br><br>(Adding 100 Str will increase your damage by 5%. So the ME belt 0.75% more damage I did not include in the calcs) <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A> at: 3/27/02 6:13:17 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 870<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 9:56:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> I'd even be sceptical if an ac40 belt would really compensate for your damage loss. I guess it would for something along the lines of an fbss, but if you get into something like silver chitin handwraps where you've got haste and stats or a db sash with higher haste and 2 ac you're looking probably at a 50 or 60 ac belt required to compensate. It's rediculously skewed towards haste.<br><br>Thanks senchy for working this out. I'd almost say put this as in the tomes of knowledge or at least senchy's piece with the statement Haste &gt; All. Here's why. or something.<br><br>It's incredibly obvious when you look at the numbers. And if you are so worried about the big loss from your axgoreth's belt, a very good combo is silver chitin handwraps and axgoreth. They give nice ac, resists str and wis and 22% haste.<br><br>Haste &gt; all. I feel really sorry for the folks who are using no haste and a 1 hander and shield. You probably have a huge amount of ac and have no idea why you can't take on mobs that a 2 hander hasted pally with 100ac less can rip apart.<br><br>I'd use fbss with a 30/40 no stat axe over an axgoreth belt 20ac, sbs 25ac and lsoee 15ac. Which would net me a loss of 60raw ac. That's almost 100ac gained in total. And in fact I have had basically that option and chose the haste and 2 hander. (well, db sash and 30/36 but close enough..) because I was getting eaten by mobs.<br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urekcim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rekcim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 11:37:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> A paladins weakest link is damage output.  Haste helps us do more damage, thus making us more complete as a class in eq.  If you don't use a haste item, then you have NO CLUE about how eq works.  I would use a fbss over an ac 50 belt.   Haste is the MOST important stat for ANY melee/hybrid period.  Ac is important, AFTER getting proper haste.<br><br>BTW a haste item will stack with a haste spell.  If you have an enchanter in the group, you still are doint 21% more damage with the fbss on then without it.  NOw remember that a FBSS is the MINIIMUM haste item you should own.  The ultimate goal is to get a 36-40% item(cof etc).   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=298.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=298.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=298.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=298.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=298.topic&start=101&stop=112>6</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=298.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=20><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/